FBIS4-10663 "drlat073_a_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 Caribbean Cuba British Tourism Company To Operate in Camaguey British Tourism Company To Operate in Camaguey FL1504013194 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1932 GMT 14 Apr 94 FL1504013194 Havana Radio Reloj Network Spanish BFN [Text] The British (Tour World) company will begin operations in Cuba in early May at Santa Lucia Beach on the northern coast of Camaguey. This is Great Britain's fifth largest tourism company in terms of the number of people it serves. The company will have 140 rooms in the four-star Cuatro Vientos and Caracol Hotels. The British tourists will join those who prefer the attractions of Santa Lucia beach, the bulk of whom come from Germany, Canada, The Netherlands, and Italy. Felix Moreno, regional manager of the Cubanacan S.A. Corporation, stressed that there was an increase in the number of tourists who visited this region of Camaguey in April. This region contains a little over 25 percent of Cuba's beaches.
